equation.eq:
\begin{aligned}
D_w &= E_w t_w/(1-\nu_w^2), & D_r &= E_r A_r/b_r, & D_{st} &= E_{st} A_{st}/b_{st},\\
S_r &= E_r A_r c_r/b_r, & S_{st} &= E_{st} A_{st} c_{st}/b_{st}, & K_w &= E_w t_w^3/[12(1-\nu_w^2)],\\
K_r &= E_r(I_r + A_r c_r^2)/b_r, & K_{st} &= E_{st}(I_{st}+A_{st}c_{st}^2)/b_{st}, & T_r &= G_r J_r/b_r,\\
T_{st} &= G_{st}J_{st}/b_{st}. & & & &
\end{aligned}

equation.notes:
Strain energy, general reinforced shell (concentrated stiffeners). Verified at high zoom:
    RING sum integrand carries factor s_r cos(alpha) d(theta) (note s_r = ring meridional location, not s);
    STRINGER sum integrand carries only ds (no s cos(alpha) factor). Wall (first) term identical to Eq.(14) wall term.

equation.eq:
\begin{aligned}
D_r &= E_r A_r, & D_{st} &= E_{st} A_{st}, & S_r &= E_r A_r c_r, & S_{st} &= E_{st} A_{st} c_{st},\\
K_r &= E_r(I_r + A_r c_r^2), & K_{st} &= E_{st}(I_{st}+A_{st}c_{st}^2), & T_r &= G_r J_r, & T_{st} &= G_{st}J_{st}.
\end{aligned}

T = \tfrac{1}{2}\int_{s_1}^{s_2}\!\!\int_{0}^{2\pi}\big\{ m_w(\dot{u}^2+\dot{v}^2+\dot{w}^2)\big\} s\cos\alpha\,d\theta\,ds
\;+\; \tfrac{1}{2}\sum_{r=1}^{P}\Big\{ \int_{0}^{2\pi} m_r(\dot{u}^2+\dot{v}^2+\dot{w}^2)\, s_r\cos\alpha\,d\theta \Big\}_{r}
\;+\; \tfrac{1}{2}\sum_{st=1}^{Q}\Big\{ \int_{s_1}^{s_2} m_{st}(\dot{u}^2+\dot{v}^2+\dot{w}^2)\, ds \Big\}_{st}

extraction.text:
II. EXPERIMENTAL INVESTIGATIONS. Three different stiffened shells were tested (see Fig. 3, Tables I, II):
Shell No. 1 - reinforced with three equispaced rings;
Shell No. 2 - reinforced with three equispaced rings and three equispaced stringers;
Shell No. 3 - reinforced with three equispaced rings and six equispaced stringers.
Shells machined from solid 6061 aluminum billets; rings and (for shells 2,3) stringers integral.
Defines the three configurations referenced by the theory parameters P (rings) and Q (stringers).
